Pfizer, Apple Inc. share gains lead Dow's nearly 400-point rally

The Dow Jones Industrial Average is rallying Monday morning with shares of Pfizer and Apple Inc. delivering strong returns for the index. The Dow DJIA, -1.14% was most recently trading 393 points higher (1.5%), as shares of Pfizer PFE, -0.23% and Apple Inc. AAPL, -5.70% are contributing to the index's intraday rally. Pfizer's shares are up $1.43, or 4.2%, while those of Apple Inc. have climbed $14.18 (3.7%), combining for a roughly 107-point bump for the Dow. UnitedHealth UNH, 0.36%, Home Depot HD, -1.36%, and Johnson & Johnson JNJ, -0.64% are also contributing significantly to the gain. A $1 move in any of the index's 30 components equates to a 6.86-point swing.

